      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A concerned father rushes his 13-year-old son to the emergency department from school due to 2 days of persistent nausea, vomiting, and diarrhea. The boy is in evident distress, experiencing severe pain upon palpation of the abdomen, particularly in the right lower quadrant (RLQ). He describes the pain as initially starting around the periumbilical area before localizing to the RLQ. The boy is tachycardic, febrile, and presents with mild hypertension. Physical examination reveals diffuse abdominal tenderness with notable rebound tenderness in the RLQ, leading to a clinical diagnosis of appendicitis. Among the following statements about appendicitis, which one is correct?</span></span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q3681763",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
